    • Method Detail

      • initialize

        public void initialize​(java.net.URL url,
                       java.util.ResourceBundle resourceBundle)
        This method sets the top part list and the lower associated parts table views. The upper list will contain any parts that are available in the parts inventory. The lower list will contain any parts that are currently associated with the product.
        Specified by:
        initialize in interface javafx.fxml.Initializable
        Parameters:
        url - url
        resourceBundle - resourceBundle

      • toMain

        public void toMain​(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent)
            throws java.io.IOException
        The method will send the user back to the mainController screen without altering any of the data with the selected product.
        Parameters:
        actionEvent - clicking the cancel button.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - IOException

      • receiveProductData

        public void receiveProductData​(Product data)
        This method takes the data from the mainController screen and sends it the modifyProductForm data fields. The data populates the fields including any associated parts with that product.
        Parameters:
        data - the product data from the main controller screen.

      • onSearchParts

        public void onSearchParts​(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent)
        This method searches the Parts inventory. If a partial match is found for either the part name or the partID then it will populate the list. If no match is found an error message will appear. If you hit enter on an empty search then the entire list of parts will repopulate.
        Parameters:
        actionEvent - adding information to the searchParts text field and hitting enter.

      • onAddPart

        public void onAddPart​(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent)
        This method will add a new associated part to the Product. The part is added to the associated parts table which shows any and all parts associated with the product.
        Parameters:
        actionEvent - clicking the add button.

      • onDeletePart

        public void onDeletePart​(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent)
        This method will delete an associated part from the lower table which is the parts that are associated with the currently selected product. The part is removed from the product but remains a part of the part inventory.
        Parameters:
        actionEvent - clicking the remove associated part button.

      • onSaveProduct

        public void onSaveProduct​(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent)
                   throws java.io.IOException
        This method will modify the existing products information once the save button is clicked. The information is updated to the new information inputed in the text fields of the modifyProductForm screen. The productId text field can not be changed and is used to replace the existing product infomation in the mainController Screen.
        Parameters:
        actionEvent - clicking the save button
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - IOException
